<br>
Ceramic vaned arrows (triv 202) also sell back for more than components so when you start failing few times, you can make money on them (ut-oh, shouldn't have given the secret).  I had heard much the same about Shaped Shadewood Compound (2 cam) bows, but not significantly greater and that bow is a &lt;250 triv so the success rate wasn't something I wanted to risk (I think the components, if you don't get a pile of tinkered cams, is around 400-500 plat.. can't remember off-hand) since the sell back is not higher than the component costs of 2 (just a small bit more than 1).  <br>
<br>
I am not looking to fletching to make plat... that was never the intent.  I jsut want the uber wood elf bow *impish grin*.<br>
<br>
